Bug.WithStack:
Build id: 200302131253
Create a new class, check the "public static void main(String[] args)" checkbox in the wizard. Put the cursor after the method declaration, hit enter. The cursor is now inside the method, on a blank line, tabbed to the right of the method declaration. Now type "for", hit Ctrl-space, and select "iterate - over a collection". Hit the right arrow followed by the delete key (to do compact assignment). Both of the '.' characters following the "iter" variable in the other parts of the for loop get removed, resulting in the following.
for (Iterator iter= collection.iterator(); iterhasNext();) { type element = (type) iternext();
} This works now.

